  "prompt": "Where did Adam and Eve live?",
  "response": "According to the Bible, Adam and Eve lived in the Garden of Eden. The Garden of Eden is described in the Book of Genesis as a paradise created by God, located in the east, often associated with abundant flora and fauna. The exact location of the Garden of Eden is not specified in the biblical text and has been the subject of speculation and interpretation for centuries. Some traditions suggest it may be near the confluence of the Tigris and Euphrates rivers, in present-day Iraq, but there is no definitive archaeological evidence to confirm its exact location.",
